    "created_at": "2015-03-31T03:32:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-31T03:32:51Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Unfortunately, the TD of a head block can only be calculated once the block  is connected to the blockchain, ie after we downloaded the entire chain leading to this head. Our best bet to achieve this is to follow the chain back by requesting blockhashes from the best peer. \nTherefore we need to rely on the advertised TD. \nTo mitigate against a malicious peer misadvertising a higher TD, we calculate the TD on insertion and match it to the td advertised by the peer. If there is a mismatch, the peer is suspended. \nSo, we check the TD at the earliest possible occasion. https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/blockpool/section.go#L150\nIf initial PoW checking proves insufficient against malicious peer invalid \"infinite\" chains, we could apply a voting scheme, ie. requiring X percent of peers to agree on the root block  of the best peer's head section. However this may prove too restrictive if connectivity is sparse.\n",
